<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="139" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,151,536]" pageId="4" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,332,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="139">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species could be easily distinguished from other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1100,1217,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1100,1217,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="139">Megaselia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the base of fore metatarsus with a conspicuous notch. In the key of 
<bibRefCitation author="Schmitz" box="[729,1007,367,392]" pageId="4" pageNumber="139" refString="Schmitz, H. &amp; Beyer, E. (1965) Phoridae, In: Lindner, E. (Ed.), Die Fliegen der Palaearktischen Region. Lief. 258. E. Schweizerbart'sche Verlagsbuchhandlung, Stuttgart, pp. 513 - 560. [in German]" type="journal article" year="1965">
Schmitz &amp; Beyer (
<number box="[940,998,367,392]" pageId="4" pageNumber="139" value="1965.0">1965</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName box="[1014,1206,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lacunitarsalis">
<emphasis box="[1014,1206,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="139">M. lacunitarsalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
will run to 
<taxonomicName authority="Schmitz" authorityName="Schmitz" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="furva">
<emphasis box="[1339,1436,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="139">M. furva</emphasis>
Schmitz
</taxonomicName>
at couplet 
<number box="[366,394,404,428]" pageId="4" pageNumber="139" value="88.0">88</number>
of Group IV. However, the latter with equal supra-antennal bristles and lower supra-antennal bristles vertically below upper pair. In the key to British 
<taxonomicName authority="Disney, 1989" authorityName="Disney" authorityYear="1989" box="[846,1149,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[846,963,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="139">Megaselia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Disney" box="[984,1140,439,464]" pageId="4" pageNumber="139" refString="Disney, R. H. L. (1989) Scuttle Flies-Diptera, Phoridae, Genus Megaselia. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects, 10 (8), 1 - 155." type="journal article" year="1989">
Disney, 
<number box="[1083,1140,440,464]" pageId="4" pageNumber="139" value="1989.0">1989</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
this species runs to 
<taxonomicName authority="Wood" authorityName="Wood" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unguicularis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="139">M. unguicularis</emphasis>
(Wood)
</taxonomicName>
at couplet 
<number box="[509,554,476,501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="139" value="126.0">126</number>
. Both species with short anal tube, but left side of epandrium of the latter with more than 
<number box="[270,298,512,536]" pageId="4" pageNumber="139" value="10.0">10</number>
bristles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
